WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.880 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.880 --> 00:00:08.330 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:08.330 --> 00:00:19.587 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.587 --> 00:00:21.170 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA GARR: "Men
are from Mars, Women

00:00:21.170 --> 00:00:24.080 align:middle line:10%
are from Venus" is arguably
the best-selling relationship

00:00:24.080 --> 00:00:26.450 align:middle line:10%
book of all time,
with 50 million copies

00:00:26.450 --> 00:00:29.750 align:middle line:10%
in print 100 countries
and 45 languages,

00:00:29.750 --> 00:00:31.380 align:middle line:10%
and still going strong.

00:00:31.380 --> 00:00:33.800 align:middle line:84%
It's been listed as one of
the most influential books

00:00:33.800 --> 00:00:35.730 align:middle line:90%
of the last quarter century.

00:00:35.730 --> 00:00:37.260 align:middle line:10%
And John Gray is with us today.

00:00:37.260 --> 00:00:40.250 align:middle line:10%
He's appeared on "Oprah" and
"Larry King Live" and CNN,

00:00:40.250 --> 00:00:43.980 align:middle line:10%
among many other shows,
for the past 40 years.

00:00:43.980 --> 00:00:46.160 align:middle line:10%
In his new book,
"Beyond Mars and Venus,"

00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:50.390 align:middle line:10%
John explains why being a man
or a woman in today's society

00:00:50.390 --> 00:00:52.920 align:middle line:10%
is more complex than ever.

00:00:52.920 --> 00:00:54.210 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for joining us.

00:00:54.210 --> 00:00:55.670 align:middle line:84%
>>JOHN GRAY: I am so
happy to be with you.

00:00:55.670 --> 00:00:56.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:00:56.470 --> 00:00:59.490 align:middle line:84%
There are so many questions
that go along with relationships

00:00:59.490 --> 00:01:00.290 align:middle line:90%
today.

00:01:00.290 --> 00:01:04.010 align:middle line:84%
What has changed since you
wrote the book in the '90s?

00:01:04.010 --> 00:01:06.110 align:middle line:10%
>>GRAY: Well,
actually it started

00:01:06.110 --> 00:01:07.610 align:middle line:10%
happening I think in the '60s.

00:01:07.610 --> 00:01:09.910 align:middle line:10%
Because I grew up in
the '60s, a teenager.

00:01:09.910 --> 00:01:12.450 align:middle line:10%
I grew out my hair like a girl.

00:01:12.450 --> 00:01:14.360 align:middle line:90%
I had bell-bottom pants, boots.

00:01:14.360 --> 00:01:15.500 align:middle line:90%
I demonstrated for peace.

00:01:15.500 --> 00:01:16.760 align:middle line:90%
What was happening?

00:01:16.760 --> 00:01:20.840 align:middle line:84%
I was liberated from being just
a traditional male to moving

00:01:20.840 --> 00:01:23.780 align:middle line:84%
onto my more loving self,
my more feminine self,

00:01:23.780 --> 00:01:25.100 align:middle line:90%
becoming whole.

00:01:25.100 --> 00:01:28.467 align:middle line:84%
And as I shifted from masculine
to feminine, it was ecstatic.

00:01:28.467 --> 00:01:30.050 align:middle line:84%
Meanwhile, all the
women were shifting

00:01:30.050 --> 00:01:33.140 align:middle line:84%
from being traditional women
to being empowerment groups.

00:01:33.140 --> 00:01:35.420 align:middle line:84%
We're going to be
heads of corporations.

00:01:35.420 --> 00:01:36.420 align:middle line:90%
We want to this power.

00:01:36.420 --> 00:01:37.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Rosie the Riveter.

00:01:37.160 --> 00:01:39.440 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Make a difference,
become President, all that.

00:01:39.440 --> 00:01:42.080 align:middle line:84%
So they're experiencing
the ecstasy of release

00:01:42.080 --> 00:01:44.960 align:middle line:84%
from this limitation
of being on one side.

00:01:44.960 --> 00:01:46.310 align:middle line:90%
Spirit released us.

00:01:46.310 --> 00:01:48.350 align:middle line:84%
Now we can connect with
our true self, which

00:01:48.350 --> 00:01:50.000 align:middle line:90%
is both masculine feminine.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:52.460 align:middle line:84%
And so as you become
more close to wholeness,

00:01:52.460 --> 00:01:53.390 align:middle line:90%
you feel fantastic.

00:01:53.390 --> 00:01:54.860 align:middle line:84%
That's where the
creativity comes,

00:01:54.860 --> 00:01:57.050 align:middle line:84%
that's where power comes,
that's where love comes,

00:01:57.050 --> 00:01:58.940 align:middle line:84%
that's where lasting
passion comes,

00:01:58.940 --> 00:02:01.580 align:middle line:84%
when you have both
masculine and feminine.

00:02:01.580 --> 00:02:03.890 align:middle line:84%
However, we have
physical bodies and we

00:02:03.890 --> 00:02:05.810 align:middle line:84%
have to honor-- if
I have a male body,

00:02:05.810 --> 00:02:08.479 align:middle line:84%
I have to make sure I stay
grounded in my masculine body.

00:02:08.479 --> 00:02:11.030 align:middle line:84%
And women have to be grounded
in their female hormones.

00:02:11.030 --> 00:02:12.110 align:middle line:90%
Actually, very hormonal.

00:02:12.110 --> 00:02:13.670 align:middle line:90%
The whole thing is hormonal.

00:02:13.670 --> 00:02:16.730 align:middle line:84%
Male hormones, female
hormones, and if I go too far

00:02:16.730 --> 00:02:19.640 align:middle line:84%
to the female side, then
I become angry, irritable,

00:02:19.640 --> 00:02:21.322 align:middle line:90%
depressed, and I waste time.

00:02:21.322 --> 00:02:23.280 align:middle line:84%
For women, if they go
too far to the male side,

00:02:23.280 --> 00:02:25.220 align:middle line:84%
they're very
confident, powerful,

00:02:25.220 --> 00:02:28.050 align:middle line:84%
but they can't sleep at night,
or they can't fall in love.

00:02:28.050 --> 00:02:29.510 align:middle line:90%
They can't relax.

00:02:29.510 --> 00:02:30.860 align:middle line:90%
So busy, busy, busy.

00:02:30.860 --> 00:02:33.470 align:middle line:84%
So these are symptoms
of imbalance.

00:02:33.470 --> 00:02:35.790 align:middle line:84%
So by understanding
it's a good thing,

00:02:35.790 --> 00:02:38.240 align:middle line:84%
we've got a whole new set of
problems and relationships.

00:02:38.240 --> 00:02:40.070 align:middle line:84%
By understanding
this, relationships

00:02:40.070 --> 00:02:41.990 align:middle line:90%
can help us find that balance.

00:02:41.990 --> 00:02:45.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So because we have
a different level of growth

00:02:45.120 --> 00:02:48.920 align:middle line:84%
now-- we are more
evolved as a human race

00:02:48.920 --> 00:02:51.530 align:middle line:84%
about different things
around consciousness--

00:02:51.530 --> 00:02:54.150 align:middle line:90%
our environment, morality.

00:02:54.150 --> 00:02:56.720 align:middle line:84%
It's definitely an increasing
level of consciousness

00:02:56.720 --> 00:02:57.620 align:middle line:90%
that we're in.

00:02:57.620 --> 00:03:01.200 align:middle line:84%
Do you think that this has
affected relationships?

00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:02.000 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Of course.

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:03.458 align:middle line:84%
Even all of our
emotional issues--

00:03:03.458 --> 00:03:05.000 align:middle line:84%
so many emotional
issues people have,

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:06.470 align:middle line:90%
go to therapists and all that.

00:03:06.470 --> 00:03:08.450 align:middle line:84%
That's actually a step
in the right direction

00:03:08.450 --> 00:03:11.030 align:middle line:84%
because now we have
more self-reflection.

00:03:11.030 --> 00:03:13.010 align:middle line:84%
Instead of just being
numb to what's going on

00:03:13.010 --> 00:03:17.240 align:middle line:84%
and unconsciously acting out
patterns of drama in our lives,

00:03:17.240 --> 00:03:18.270 align:middle line:90%
we can reflect.

00:03:18.270 --> 00:03:21.020 align:middle line:84%
We can step back and look
at what's going on inside.

00:03:21.020 --> 00:03:24.680 align:middle line:84%
And where I see the key factor
is in our relationships.

00:03:24.680 --> 00:03:26.150 align:middle line:90%
You can't hide from yourself.

00:03:26.150 --> 00:03:28.700 align:middle line:84%
Your partner is going to push
every button inside of you.

00:03:28.700 --> 00:03:30.010 align:middle line:84%
When you're out of
balance, it's going

00:03:30.010 --> 00:03:31.895 align:middle line:84%
to show up in your relationship
more than anything.

00:03:31.895 --> 00:03:32.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Isn't that true?

00:03:32.600 --> 00:03:32.875 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:03:32.875 --> 00:03:34.292 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Yeah, and
so what we do is

00:03:34.292 --> 00:03:36.530 align:middle line:84%
we have to learn, OK, what
are the symptoms of being

00:03:36.530 --> 00:03:37.230 align:middle line:90%
out of balance?

00:03:37.230 --> 00:03:39.260 align:middle line:84%
How do I come back into balance
and what does that look like,

00:03:39.260 --> 00:03:41.840 align:middle line:84%
and what does that mean, and
what are the benefits of that?

00:03:41.840 --> 00:03:43.370 align:middle line:84%
And quite simply,
what I can say,

00:03:43.370 --> 00:03:45.320 align:middle line:84%
after 33 years of
marriage, the benefits

00:03:45.320 --> 00:03:48.110 align:middle line:84%
of learning to continually
use your relationships--

00:03:48.110 --> 00:03:50.540 align:middle line:84%
primarily intimate,
but all relationships--

00:03:50.540 --> 00:03:53.720 align:middle line:84%
to come back into balance, in
your intimate relationships,

00:03:53.720 --> 00:03:56.510 align:middle line:84%
you can experience
lasting, romantic passion.

00:03:56.510 --> 00:03:58.047 align:middle line:90%
That is a possibility.

00:03:58.047 --> 00:03:59.630 align:middle line:84%
Younger generation
today says, I don't

00:03:59.630 --> 00:04:01.020 align:middle line:90%
know if it's a possibility.

00:04:01.020 --> 00:04:02.840 align:middle line:84%
It just goes, it
goes, and it goes.

00:04:02.840 --> 00:04:04.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And younger people
are waiting longer and longer

00:04:04.790 --> 00:04:05.420 align:middle line:90%
to get married.

00:04:05.420 --> 00:04:07.310 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Well, what happens
is that they get together

00:04:07.310 --> 00:04:08.300 align:middle line:90%
and the passion goes away.

00:04:08.300 --> 00:04:09.630 align:middle line:84%
They're friends,
they like each other.

00:04:09.630 --> 00:04:11.390 align:middle line:84%
They don't even have to have
a lot of reasons sometimes.

00:04:11.390 --> 00:04:14.030 align:middle line:84%
But it just-- the juice
isn't there, so they move on

00:04:14.030 --> 00:04:14.840 align:middle line:90%
and move on.

00:04:14.840 --> 00:04:17.690 align:middle line:84%
And why the juice isn't there,
why that attraction isn't

00:04:17.690 --> 00:04:21.050 align:middle line:84%
there, that's what we can
learn by learning new skills,

00:04:21.050 --> 00:04:23.990 align:middle line:84%
how to create that lasting
love, that lasting connection.

00:04:23.990 --> 00:04:26.510 align:middle line:84%
And what's interesting is
if you go back 50 years,

00:04:26.510 --> 00:04:28.730 align:middle line:84%
people didn't really care
if the passion went away.

00:04:28.730 --> 00:04:29.605 align:middle line:90%
That was normal.

00:04:29.605 --> 00:04:30.980 align:middle line:84%
Go back hundreds
of years, people

00:04:30.980 --> 00:04:32.917 align:middle line:84%
didn't even know what
passion was, basically.

00:04:32.917 --> 00:04:34.250 align:middle line:90%
And often women will say to me--

00:04:34.250 --> 00:04:34.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:04:34.690 --> 00:04:35.660 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Yeah.

00:04:35.660 --> 00:04:37.820 align:middle line:90%
Romeo and Juliet, OK, passion.

00:04:37.820 --> 00:04:40.850 align:middle line:84%
Because they died the day
after they got married.

00:04:40.850 --> 00:04:43.680 align:middle line:84%
It was standard policy that you
lose attraction to your partner

00:04:43.680 --> 00:04:44.480 align:middle line:90%
after a while.

00:04:44.480 --> 00:04:46.730 align:middle line:84%
When you got married, it
was always, does he make--

00:04:46.730 --> 00:04:49.370 align:middle line:84%
you know, you look at
the basic characteristics

00:04:49.370 --> 00:04:50.990 align:middle line:90%
for survival and security.

00:04:50.990 --> 00:04:53.790 align:middle line:84%
But once we're able to
provide that for ourselves,

00:04:53.790 --> 00:04:56.300 align:middle line:84%
our needs shift to
wanting a higher

00:04:56.300 --> 00:05:00.290 align:middle line:84%
level of emotional fulfillment,
which then shifts into a higher

00:05:00.290 --> 00:05:02.360 align:middle line:90%
level of self-actualization.

00:05:02.360 --> 00:05:04.430 align:middle line:84%
And people who want
passionate marriages, that's

00:05:04.430 --> 00:05:05.720 align:middle line:90%
called self-actualization.

00:05:05.720 --> 00:05:07.375 align:middle line:84%
That's bringing
forth the genius.

00:05:07.375 --> 00:05:08.750 align:middle line:84%
Because historically,
nobody ever

00:05:08.750 --> 00:05:11.270 align:middle line:84%
had lasting passion in marriage,
or it was extremely rare.

00:05:11.270 --> 00:05:13.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Kings and queens had
separate bedrooms and, yeah,

00:05:13.700 --> 00:05:14.060 align:middle line:90%
I mean--

00:05:14.060 --> 00:05:16.227 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Oh, there was nothing
going on between them.

00:05:16.227 --> 00:05:18.830 align:middle line:84%
That's a-- you know, King
Arthur and Guinevere--

00:05:18.830 --> 00:05:19.630 align:middle line:90%
it was Lancelot.

00:05:19.630 --> 00:05:20.910 align:middle line:84%
And of course, that
was short-lived.

00:05:20.910 --> 00:05:21.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Exactly.

00:05:21.090 --> 00:05:22.715 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: It's always
the unavailable guy

00:05:22.715 --> 00:05:23.810 align:middle line:90%
that has the passion.

00:05:23.810 --> 00:05:24.690 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't last.

00:05:24.690 --> 00:05:26.460 align:middle line:90%
But you can make it last.

00:05:26.460 --> 00:05:28.170 align:middle line:90%
And here's the dynamic.

00:05:28.170 --> 00:05:29.790 align:middle line:90%
People say, why does it go away?

00:05:29.790 --> 00:05:32.400 align:middle line:84%
Well, when there's newness,
it stimulates a brain chemical

00:05:32.400 --> 00:05:33.250 align:middle line:90%
called dopamine.

00:05:33.250 --> 00:05:35.070 align:middle line:84%
Dopamine gives you
passion, excitement.

00:05:35.070 --> 00:05:36.150 align:middle line:90%
Oh, you just went somewhere new.

00:05:36.150 --> 00:05:36.900 align:middle line:90%
You get excited.

00:05:36.900 --> 00:05:38.820 align:middle line:84%
And then you see the
same thing over and over,

00:05:38.820 --> 00:05:39.620 align:middle line:90%
you get used to it.

00:05:39.620 --> 00:05:41.730 align:middle line:90%
Familiarity kills passion.

00:05:41.730 --> 00:05:44.130 align:middle line:84%
So you always can
find familiarity--

00:05:44.130 --> 00:05:46.590 align:middle line:84%
I mean, newness in
a new relationship.

00:05:46.590 --> 00:05:47.640 align:middle line:90%
That's going to go away.

00:05:47.640 --> 00:05:47.894 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's easy.

00:05:47.894 --> 00:05:49.644 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: You get to
that nice comfort zone.

00:05:49.644 --> 00:05:51.460 align:middle line:90%
OK, comfort zone is good too.

00:05:51.460 --> 00:05:53.070 align:middle line:90%
So how do you keep the passion?

00:05:53.070 --> 00:05:54.330 align:middle line:90%
Polarity.

00:05:54.330 --> 00:05:57.180 align:middle line:84%
When you recognize that
women and men are different,

00:05:57.180 --> 00:06:00.360 align:middle line:84%
and women can connect with the
essence of their femininity,

00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:03.000 align:middle line:84%
men can connect to the
essence of their masculinity,

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:04.350 align:middle line:90%
they always want to connect.

00:06:04.350 --> 00:06:07.060 align:middle line:84%
Polarity can create
passion for a lifetime

00:06:07.060 --> 00:06:08.620 align:middle line:90%
if you're able to maintain it.

00:06:08.620 --> 00:06:11.100 align:middle line:84%
But if you give up who you
are, your authentic self,

00:06:11.100 --> 00:06:13.410 align:middle line:84%
to make a relationship
work, it goes flat.

00:06:13.410 --> 00:06:15.160 align:middle line:84%
You have a comfortable
relationship.

00:06:15.160 --> 00:06:16.827 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How do you
add stress into that,

00:06:16.827 --> 00:06:18.780 align:middle line:84%
when you have double-income
families and aging

00:06:18.780 --> 00:06:21.030 align:middle line:90%
parents and young children?

00:06:21.030 --> 00:06:22.143 align:middle line:90%
That's a catastrophe.

00:06:22.143 --> 00:06:23.310 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: It is a catastrophe.

00:06:23.310 --> 00:06:24.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:06:24.110 --> 00:06:26.520 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And let's look at it
from another point of view.

00:06:26.520 --> 00:06:30.000 align:middle line:84%
We create stress in our
life by choices we make.

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:31.110 align:middle line:90%
Take a little bit--

00:06:31.110 --> 00:06:32.850 align:middle line:90%
come back to responsibility.

00:06:32.850 --> 00:06:35.610 align:middle line:84%
For example, our
expectations of perfection,

00:06:35.610 --> 00:06:37.683 align:middle line:84%
expectations of doing
everything the right way.

00:06:37.683 --> 00:06:38.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's so true, yes.

00:06:38.850 --> 00:06:42.060 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: That is us creating
a drama in our life.

00:06:42.060 --> 00:06:43.890 align:middle line:84%
And often, you
know, many women--

00:06:43.890 --> 00:06:45.780 align:middle line:90%
we did one study on women--

00:06:45.780 --> 00:06:51.030 align:middle line:84%
wives whose husbands
did wash the dishes.

00:06:51.030 --> 00:06:53.370 align:middle line:84%
And they complained that
the men did it so poorly

00:06:53.370 --> 00:06:54.830 align:middle line:90%
they had to wash them again.

00:06:54.830 --> 00:06:55.130 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:06:55.130 --> 00:06:55.670 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:06:55.670 --> 00:06:57.753 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Of course, that's
why the men don't do it.

00:06:57.753 --> 00:06:59.410 align:middle line:84%
Because they're going
to get yelled at.

00:06:59.410 --> 00:07:00.630 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: There's a part
of that to be true.

00:07:00.630 --> 00:07:03.000 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of stuff
that comes along with that.

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:04.975 align:middle line:84%
We haven't seen our
fathers doing dishes.

00:07:04.975 --> 00:07:06.600 align:middle line:84%
We didn't see our
fathers doing dishes.

00:07:06.600 --> 00:07:07.500 align:middle line:90%
We didn't really learn how.

00:07:07.500 --> 00:07:09.630 align:middle line:84%
We don't get a lot of
acknowledgment for that.

00:07:09.630 --> 00:07:11.570 align:middle line:84%
Men are always driven
by what is going

00:07:11.570 --> 00:07:13.890 align:middle line:84%
to get the most acknowledgment
because we know,

00:07:13.890 --> 00:07:17.100 align:middle line:84%
even today, deep down inside,
if you don't perform well

00:07:17.100 --> 00:07:18.018 align:middle line:90%
in the world--

00:07:18.018 --> 00:07:19.560 align:middle line:84%
making money is the
way it looks now.

00:07:19.560 --> 00:07:22.620 align:middle line:84%
If you don't have some skill
or task that's admirable and--

00:07:22.620 --> 00:07:23.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's a reward.

00:07:23.690 --> 00:07:25.440 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: --to get the
reward and the reward

00:07:25.440 --> 00:07:26.670 align:middle line:90%
is a woman will love you.

00:07:26.670 --> 00:07:29.370 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, deeper down,
this is politically incorrect,

00:07:29.370 --> 00:07:31.980 align:middle line:84%
but it's true, deeper
down, she'll love you

00:07:31.980 --> 00:07:34.590 align:middle line:84%
and she'll take off her
clothes and have sex with you.

00:07:34.590 --> 00:07:35.980 align:middle line:90%
That is the ultimate for men.

00:07:35.980 --> 00:07:36.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's the root.

