quick, how relationships really

00:14:55.290 --> 00:14:57.060 align:middle line:90%
boils down to chemistry.

00:14:57.060 --> 00:14:58.200 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Oh, yeah.

00:14:58.200 --> 00:15:00.240 align:middle line:84%
I mean, everything is
more than just chemistry.

00:15:00.240 --> 00:15:01.710 align:middle line:90%
We have spirit, we have a mind.

00:15:01.710 --> 00:15:04.410 align:middle line:84%
But the bottom line is we
live in this house here

00:15:04.410 --> 00:15:05.340 align:middle line:90%
and it's affected.

00:15:05.340 --> 00:15:07.570 align:middle line:84%
You can have all the spiritual
insights in the world,

00:15:07.570 --> 00:15:09.990 align:middle line:84%
and if you're deficient
in the right hormones,

00:15:09.990 --> 00:15:11.520 align:middle line:90%
you're going to be depressed.

00:15:11.520 --> 00:15:13.920 align:middle line:84%
And a big
misunderstanding-- this

00:15:13.920 --> 00:15:16.160 align:middle line:84%
is a great takeaway
from our conversation--

00:15:16.160 --> 00:15:19.040 align:middle line:84%
is when you think about men's
aggression and bad behavior--

00:15:19.040 --> 00:15:21.620 align:middle line:84%
selfish behavior and so
forth, hurtful behavior,

00:15:21.620 --> 00:15:24.860 align:middle line:84%
being mean, not caring,
being abusive-- this happens.

00:15:24.860 --> 00:15:26.900 align:middle line:84%
And if you look at
what's happening in men,

00:15:26.900 --> 00:15:29.030 align:middle line:84%
everybody thinks
it's testosterone.

00:15:29.030 --> 00:15:30.500 align:middle line:90%
But actually, it's not.

00:15:30.500 --> 00:15:33.260 align:middle line:84%
Any man who is
aggressive, angry, upset,

00:15:33.260 --> 00:15:36.480 align:middle line:84%
mean, his testosterone
is actually going down

00:15:36.480 --> 00:15:38.420 align:middle line:90%
and his estrogen is going up.

00:15:38.420 --> 00:15:40.370 align:middle line:84%
When men go too far
to the female side,

00:15:40.370 --> 00:15:41.930 align:middle line:90%
they become dysfunctional.

00:15:41.930 --> 00:15:43.970 align:middle line:84%
When women go too
far to the male side,

00:15:43.970 --> 00:15:45.620 align:middle line:90%
they become unloving.

00:15:45.620 --> 00:15:48.230 align:middle line:84%
You can't love if you're
not on your female side.

00:15:48.230 --> 00:15:51.780 align:middle line:84%
But if men are too much on the
female side, they can't love.

00:15:51.780 --> 00:15:54.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, there's no excuse
for a man being aggressive

00:15:54.800 --> 00:15:56.340 align:middle line:90%
and et cetera with a woman.

00:15:56.340 --> 00:15:57.545 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: We're just
explaining the biology.

00:15:57.545 --> 00:15:58.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, we're
just explaining-- yeah.

00:15:58.700 --> 00:16:00.117 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: But let's
learn from that.

00:16:00.117 --> 00:16:02.110 align:middle line:84%
Let's learn from
big arguments, OK?

00:16:02.110 --> 00:16:03.620 align:middle line:90%
And this is like--

00:16:03.620 --> 00:16:05.120 align:middle line:84%
unless you understand
the difference

00:16:05.120 --> 00:16:07.470 align:middle line:84%
between men and women,
this would not make sense.

00:16:07.470 --> 00:16:09.303 align:middle line:84%
But if you're in an
argument with your wife,

00:16:09.303 --> 00:16:12.620 align:middle line:84%
if you're a man, you need
to realize, stop talking.

00:16:12.620 --> 00:16:16.730 align:middle line:84%
Because when you're upset, when
you have emotions and you talk,

00:16:16.730 --> 00:16:18.770 align:middle line:90%
then your estrogen will go up.

00:16:18.770 --> 00:16:20.240 align:middle line:84%
This why women
come to therapists.

00:16:20.240 --> 00:16:22.160 align:middle line:84%
They get to talk
about their feelings.

00:16:22.160 --> 00:16:25.100 align:middle line:84%
90% of the people who will pay
to just have someone listen

00:16:25.100 --> 00:16:28.340 align:middle line:84%
to your feelings is because
if you're low on estrogen,

00:16:28.340 --> 00:16:30.410 align:middle line:84%
go talk about your
feelings to somebody.

00:16:30.410 --> 00:16:33.230 align:middle line:84%
Let them enter into
you, penetrate into you,

00:16:33.230 --> 00:16:34.790 align:middle line:90%
and hear you with empathy.

00:16:34.790 --> 00:16:37.460 align:middle line:84%
Your estrogen levels will go
up and your cortisol levels

00:16:37.460 --> 00:16:38.570 align:middle line:90%
will go down.

00:16:38.570 --> 00:16:40.970 align:middle line:84%
Hormonal balance
lowers cortisol.

00:16:40.970 --> 00:16:43.130 align:middle line:84%
When you have elevated
cortisol, your hormones

00:16:43.130 --> 00:16:44.130 align:middle line:90%
are out of balance.

00:16:44.130 --> 00:16:46.400 align:middle line:84%
So we're back to, in our
stressful times, well,

00:16:46.400 --> 00:16:50.420 align:middle line:84%
part of how we create stressful
lives by the expectations

00:16:50.420 --> 00:16:53.570 align:middle line:84%
and the requirements that we
have in order to feel good

00:16:53.570 --> 00:16:55.280 align:middle line:84%
or to feel lovable
or to get happiness

00:16:55.280 --> 00:16:57.530 align:middle line:84%
or whatever, we have
all these standards.

00:16:57.530 --> 00:17:00.480 align:middle line:84%
They are created from
hormonal imbalance.

00:17:00.480 --> 00:17:02.030 align:middle line:90%
And then we experience stress.

00:17:02.030 --> 00:17:04.280 align:middle line:84%
Our choices-- the
choices we make

00:17:04.280 --> 00:17:05.902 align:middle line:90%
tend to come from our hormones.

00:17:05.902 --> 00:17:07.819 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So are you saying
that it's not really

00:17:07.819 --> 00:17:10.140 align:middle line:84%
the nature of men and women
having a difficult time

00:17:10.140 --> 00:17:10.940 align:middle line:90%
communicating?

00:17:10.940 --> 00:17:12.800 align:middle line:84%
It's because our
hormones are so out

00:17:12.800 --> 00:17:15.420 align:middle line:84%
of balance because of
our stressful lives

00:17:15.420 --> 00:17:18.109 align:middle line:84%
that it then impacts
the communication.

00:17:18.109 --> 00:17:18.920 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: That, too.

00:17:18.920 --> 00:17:20.420 align:middle line:84%
I'm saying-- that
actually is another way

00:17:20.420 --> 00:17:21.319 align:middle line:90%
of saying what I said.

00:17:21.319 --> 00:17:21.589 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:17:21.589 --> 00:17:23.180 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: But what
I'm saying is often

00:17:23.180 --> 00:17:26.150 align:middle line:84%
we say the stress is causing
the problem, and what I'm saying

00:17:26.150 --> 00:17:29.480 align:middle line:84%
is the choices we make based
upon hormonal imbalance,

00:17:29.480 --> 00:17:31.380 align:middle line:84%
not knowing how to
balance our hormones.

00:17:31.380 --> 00:17:33.083 align:middle line:84%
This is a new thing
we have to learn,

00:17:33.083 --> 00:17:34.250 align:middle line:90%
how to balance our hormones.

00:17:34.250 --> 00:17:35.820 align:middle line:84%
We all know hormones
are out of balance.

00:17:35.820 --> 00:17:38.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's not through taking
the hormones, though, right?

00:17:38.320 --> 00:17:40.672 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: No, not through taking--

00:17:40.672 --> 00:17:42.380 align:middle line:84%
if you take hormones,
you're not learning

00:17:42.380 --> 00:17:43.463 align:middle line:90%
how to make them yourself.

00:17:43.463 --> 00:17:46.160 align:middle line:84%
And your body is designed,
at every stage of life,

00:17:46.160 --> 00:17:48.023 align:middle line:84%
to make the right
amount of hormones.

00:17:48.023 --> 00:17:50.190 align:middle line:84%
Many women will say, oh,
I'm going through menopause

00:17:50.190 --> 00:17:51.350 align:middle line:84%
so I can't make
as much hormones.

00:17:51.350 --> 00:17:52.940 align:middle line:84%
Well, you don't make
as many hormones,

00:17:52.940 --> 00:17:54.690 align:middle line:84%
but that's not the
source of your problem.

00:17:54.690 --> 00:17:56.373 align:middle line:84%
It's the balance
of those hormones.

00:17:56.373 --> 00:17:58.040 align:middle line:84%
Because when you're
no longer at the age

00:17:58.040 --> 00:17:59.870 align:middle line:84%
where you can make
babies, your body

00:17:59.870 --> 00:18:02.000 align:middle line:84%
doesn't need as many
hormones, but it needs

00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:03.890 align:middle line:90%
the right hormonal balance.

00:18:03.890 --> 00:18:05.810 align:middle line:84%
And so it's like
learning what behaviors

00:18:05.810 --> 00:18:07.970 align:middle line:90%
stimulate female hormones?

00:18:07.970 --> 00:18:10.483 align:middle line:84%
What behaviors
stimulate male hormones?

00:18:10.483 --> 00:18:12.650 align:middle line:84%
And it's not like you should
be a traditional woman,

00:18:12.650 --> 00:18:15.890 align:middle line:84%
where most of your life is just
stimulating female hormones.

00:18:15.890 --> 00:18:16.820 align:middle line:90%
We've outgrown that.

00:18:16.820 --> 00:18:18.050 align:middle line:90%
That's too limiting.

00:18:18.050 --> 00:18:19.770 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness says,
I want to be whole.

00:18:19.770 --> 00:18:20.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:18:20.570 --> 00:18:22.850 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: So if you're going
to express your male side,

00:18:22.850 --> 00:18:24.470 align:middle line:84%
you have to learn
along the way how

00:18:24.470 --> 00:18:26.157 align:middle line:84%
to keep coming back
to your female side,

00:18:26.157 --> 00:18:27.990 align:middle line:84%
how to keep coming back
to your female side.

00:18:27.990 --> 00:18:30.380 align:middle line:84%
And a relationship
can be a safe harbor

00:18:30.380 --> 00:18:33.530 align:middle line:84%
for women to come back to
their female side, and for men

00:18:33.530 --> 00:18:37.130 align:middle line:84%
to actually rebuild their
testosterone after their day.

00:18:37.130 --> 00:18:38.400 align:middle line:90%
So here's an example.

00:18:38.400 --> 00:18:38.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:18:38.750 --> 00:18:41.083 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: So women and men,
they get in a little argument.

00:18:41.083 --> 00:18:43.420 align:middle line:84%
Couples get in these
fights, arguments.

00:18:43.420 --> 00:18:44.220 align:middle line:90%
Women and men.

00:18:44.220 --> 00:18:45.810 align:middle line:90%
There's starting to be tension.

00:18:45.810 --> 00:18:47.550 align:middle line:84%
Well, if we understand
this dynamic,

00:18:47.550 --> 00:18:49.190 align:middle line:84%
we recognize that
whenever men are

00:18:49.190 --> 00:18:53.240 align:middle line:84%
argumentative, defensive,
irritable, angry,

00:18:53.240 --> 00:18:55.300 align:middle line:84%
their testosterone
levels are going down.

00:18:55.300 --> 00:18:57.200 align:middle line:84%
Their estrogen
levels are going up.

00:18:57.200 --> 00:19:00.620 align:middle line:84%
For him to talk at that time
will only throw him further out

00:19:00.620 --> 00:19:01.830 align:middle line:90%
of balance.

00:19:01.830 --> 00:19:03.530 align:middle line:84%
And once he's in a
fight or flight mode,

00:19:03.530 --> 00:19:06.500 align:middle line:84%
for her to talk to him at that
moment will just throw her out

00:19:06.500 --> 00:19:09.380 align:middle line:84%
of balance because he cannot
hear her with empathy.

00:19:09.380 --> 00:19:12.080 align:middle line:84%
When you're in cortisol
mode, you cannot hear someone

00:19:12.080 --> 00:19:13.010 align:middle line:90%
in empathy.

00:19:13.010 --> 00:19:13.445 align:middle line:90%
So suddenly--

00:19:13.445 --> 00:19:15.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And her
testosterone's going up too.

00:19:15.260 --> 00:19:16.190 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: She has
to defend herself.

00:19:16.190 --> 00:19:18.148 align:middle line:84%
She has the raise her
sword and defend herself.

00:19:18.148 --> 00:19:19.490 align:middle line:90%
Her estrogen goes down.

00:19:19.490 --> 00:19:22.580 align:middle line:84%
She needs to find somebody
to talk to about her feelings

00:19:22.580 --> 00:19:25.190 align:middle line:84%
to open her heart again,
and go back and approach

00:19:25.190 --> 00:19:26.360 align:middle line:90%
that conversation.

00:19:26.360 --> 00:19:29.090 align:middle line:84%
He needs to stop
talking, withdraw,

00:19:29.090 --> 00:19:31.640 align:middle line:84%
do something that will
boost his testosterone-- we

00:19:31.640 --> 00:19:33.050 align:middle line:90%
can explore those things.

00:19:33.050 --> 00:19:34.490 align:middle line:90%
Boost the testosterone.

00:19:34.490 --> 00:19:36.680 align:middle line:84%
Then, when it
comes back up, he's

00:19:36.680 --> 00:19:39.680 align:middle line:84%
going to open his heart again,
reflect on what just happened,

00:19:39.680 --> 00:19:41.260 align:middle line:90%
and go back and start again.

00:19:41.260 --> 00:19:42.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So take a break.

00:19:42.260 --> 00:19:44.420 align:middle line:84%
If you're having an
argument, take a break.

00:19:44.420 --> 00:19:46.250 align:middle line:84%
Both go to your
respective corners.

00:19:46.250 --> 00:19:48.020 align:middle line:84%
One doesn't talk,
the other one talks.

00:19:48.020 --> 00:19:48.860 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: To somebody else.

00:19:48.860 --> 00:19:50.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, to somebody else.

00:19:50.010 --> 00:19:51.200 align:middle line:84%
And then come back and see if
the communication's different.

00:19:51.200 --> 00:19:52.890 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Only when you
have your heart open.

00:19:52.890 --> 00:19:54.740 align:middle line:84%
And when you come back
with your heart open,

00:19:54.740 --> 00:19:58.090 align:middle line:84%
you don't try to attack that
problem again right away.

00:19:58.090 --> 00:19:59.600 align:middle line:84%
You come back and
do loving things

00:19:59.600 --> 00:20:01.520 align:middle line:84%
so you feel safe and
comfortable again.

00:20:01.520 --> 00:20:02.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, that's nice.

00:20:02.180 --> 00:20:03.750 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: It's like in
my marriage, we just--

00:20:03.750 --> 00:20:05.740 align:middle line:84%
whenever I go to my
cave, I come back and I--

00:20:05.740 --> 00:20:08.210 align:middle line:90%
I would come back and give her--

00:20:08.210 --> 00:20:10.940 align:middle line:84%
kind of touch her on her hair
or whatever, see where she is.

00:20:10.940 --> 00:20:13.190 align:middle line:84%
If she bristles, then she's
still needing her time.

00:20:13.190 --> 00:20:13.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:20:13.990 --> 00:20:15.560 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: But she'll
melt into my hand

00:20:15.560 --> 00:20:17.990 align:middle line:84%
and then I might join in
doing something with her,

00:20:17.990 --> 00:20:20.410 align:middle line:84%
and I give her and say,
I love you so much.

00:20:20.410 --> 00:20:23.090 align:middle line:84%
And we just-- like that
whole argument didn't happen.

00:20:23.090 --> 00:20:26.303 align:middle line:84%
You just let it go back, let
yourself re-establish trust.

00:20:26.303 --> 00:20:27.970 align:middle line:84%
And then, if you're
trying to figure out

00:20:27.970 --> 00:20:29.800 align:middle line:84%
how you're going to invest
in something, or make money,

00:20:29.800 --> 00:20:31.550 align:middle line:84%
or how you're going
to treat the children,

00:20:31.550 --> 00:20:35.770 align:middle line:84%
bring that subject up again
having reflected on how you--

00:20:35.770 --> 00:20:38.350 align:middle line:84%
I would reflect on
how I have contributed

00:20:38.350 --> 00:20:39.813 align:middle line:90%
to making the problem worse.

00:20:39.813 --> 00:20:41.980 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's interesting
you say that about finances

00:20:41.980 --> 00:20:44.560 align:middle line:84%
because one of the biggest
sources of conflict

00:20:44.560 --> 00:20:46.100 align:middle line:84%
in a relationship
is money, right?

00:20:46.100 --> 00:20:46.900 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Money.

00:20:46.900 --> 00:20:49.025 align:middle line:84%
And how you raise the
children, that's another one.

00:20:49.025 --> 00:20:50.320 align:middle line:90%
And how you spend your time.

00:20:50.320 --> 00:20:52.675 align:middle line:84%
And how much housework
he's willing to help do.

00:20:52.675 --> 00:20:55.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you're saying it's
not about those issues at all.

00:20:55.240 --> 00:20:57.130 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Well, the
conflict part of it--

00:20:57.130 --> 00:21:00.748 align:middle line:84%
the tension part of it is we
start to feel not heard, OK?

00:21:00.748 --> 00:21:02.540 align:middle line:84%
Then our hormones are
going out of balance.

00:21:02.540 --> 00:21:05.140 align:middle line:84%
What men start to feel and
what women start to feel

00:21:05.140 --> 00:21:06.530 align:middle line:90%
is slightly different.

00:21:06.530 --> 00:21:08.920 align:middle line:84%
So let me come back
to hormonal imbalance.

00:21:08.920 --> 00:21:11.230 align:middle line:84%
If men need more
testosterone, what

00:21:11.230 --> 00:21:13.960 align:middle line:84%
are the kinds of love and
messages of love that men

00:21:13.960 --> 00:21:16.030 align:middle line:90%
need to rebuild testosterone?

00:21:16.030 --> 00:21:18.250 align:middle line:84%
And if a woman needs
testosterone, the same things.

00:21:18.250 --> 00:21:19.200 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Rewards.

00:21:19.200 --> 00:21:20.200 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Well, reward.

00:21:20.200 --> 00:21:23.020 align:middle line:90%
Reward to a man is appreciation.

00:21:23.020 --> 00:21:24.550 align:middle line:90%
Oh, what a good idea.

00:21:24.550 --> 00:21:25.720 align:middle line:90%
Oh, that makes sense.

00:21:25.720 --> 00:21:27.415 align:middle line:90%
All right, that's helpful.

00:21:27.415 --> 00:21:28.870 align:middle line:90%
Help me do this.

00:21:28.870 --> 00:21:31.720 align:middle line:84%
See, whenever a man
feels, I'm in a hero role,

00:21:31.720 --> 00:21:33.740 align:middle line:84%
I'm in a provider role,
I can give to you.

00:21:33.740 --> 00:21:34.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:21:34.540 --> 00:21:35.760 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Would he do
something for you?

00:21:35.760 --> 00:21:38.350 align:middle line:84%
When he can be in that place
and you're appreciating him--

00:21:38.350 --> 00:21:40.450 align:middle line:84%
because he doesn't know
he's making a difference

00:21:40.450 --> 00:21:43.110 align:middle line:84%
unless you light
up and do a Lisa.

00:21:43.110 --> 00:21:44.180 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

