oh, I'm really going

01:03:22.058 --> 01:03:23.700 align:middle line:90%
to try to pick up the milk.

01:03:23.700 --> 01:03:25.390 align:middle line:90%
But he'll forget one more time.

01:03:25.390 --> 01:03:27.557 align:middle line:84%
And then this time when he
forgets and he comes home

01:03:27.557 --> 01:03:29.432 align:middle line:84%
and you say, oh, honey,
did you get the milk?

01:03:29.432 --> 01:03:30.640 align:middle line:90%
He goes, oh, I forgot.

01:03:30.640 --> 01:03:31.600 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I forgot.

01:03:31.600 --> 01:03:33.730 align:middle line:84%
He'll feel like, I'm not
going to forget again,

01:03:33.730 --> 01:03:36.070 align:middle line:84%
and now you've got
a guy wanting harder

01:03:36.070 --> 01:03:37.475 align:middle line:90%
to remember the things you ask.

01:03:37.475 --> 01:03:39.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: As long as
she doesn't get mad.

01:03:39.100 --> 01:03:40.050 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: As long as
she doesn't get mad.

01:03:40.050 --> 01:03:40.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

01:03:40.130 --> 01:03:42.010 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: As long as she doesn't
get disappointed with him,

01:03:42.010 --> 01:03:43.900 align:middle line:84%
as long as she's not
disapproving of him.

01:03:43.900 --> 01:03:46.490 align:middle line:84%
As long as she doesn't go into,
I knew it, I can't trust you.

01:03:46.490 --> 01:03:47.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:03:47.290 --> 01:03:48.970 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: You trust he's
going to do his best.

01:03:48.970 --> 01:03:49.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:03:49.120 --> 01:03:50.600 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: But this is a
guy-- maybe he's a plumber

01:03:50.600 --> 01:03:52.390 align:middle line:84%
or maybe he's a
investor, whatever.

01:03:52.390 --> 01:03:53.392 align:middle line:90%
He's not a milk man.

01:03:53.392 --> 01:03:55.600 align:middle line:84%
That's not what he's been
conditioned to do his life,

01:03:55.600 --> 01:03:56.920 align:middle line:90%
to remember to bring milk.

01:03:56.920 --> 01:03:58.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you just ask
for something you really

01:03:58.510 --> 01:03:59.290 align:middle line:90%
don't need.

01:03:59.290 --> 01:04:01.207 align:middle line:84%
Don't expect it and you
won't be disappointed.

01:04:01.207 --> 01:04:02.603 align:middle line:90%
And then when you finally--

01:04:02.603 --> 01:04:03.520 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: When you say--

01:04:03.520 --> 01:04:05.860 align:middle line:84%
when you ask for something
you don't really need,

01:04:05.860 --> 01:04:07.528 align:middle line:90%
let's define need.

01:04:07.528 --> 01:04:09.070 align:middle line:84%
If I bring home the
milk, it actually

01:04:09.070 --> 01:04:11.110 align:middle line:90%
makes her life a little easier.

01:04:11.110 --> 01:04:13.120 align:middle line:84%
That's what you want,
is to make requests

01:04:13.120 --> 01:04:17.680 align:middle line:84%
for things that make your life
a little more easy until he gets

01:04:17.680 --> 01:04:20.200 align:middle line:84%
into the mode of
doing things for you,

01:04:20.200 --> 01:04:22.520 align:middle line:84%
knowing he's going to
get this sweet reward.

01:04:22.520 --> 01:04:24.910 align:middle line:84%
See, we're trained
as men, big things.

01:04:24.910 --> 01:04:27.000 align:middle line:84%
If you really need it,
the house is burning down,

01:04:27.000 --> 01:04:28.180 align:middle line:90%
then we get up and go.

01:04:28.180 --> 01:04:30.530 align:middle line:84%
But if it's just a
little thing, we forget.

01:04:30.530 --> 01:04:33.190 align:middle line:84%
We want to train a man,
little things get as much love

01:04:33.190 --> 01:04:34.300 align:middle line:90%
as big things.

01:04:34.300 --> 01:04:35.140 align:middle line:84%
And now, all of a
sudden, you've got

01:04:35.140 --> 01:04:37.510 align:middle line:84%
a lasting romantic relationship
where he's giving you

01:04:37.510 --> 01:04:39.100 align:middle line:84%
a little affection,
he's complimenting you,

01:04:39.100 --> 01:04:40.300 align:middle line:90%
he's looking you in the eyes.

01:04:40.300 --> 01:04:41.890 align:middle line:84%
These are little
things and women need

01:04:41.890 --> 01:04:44.680 align:middle line:84%
them to keep bumping
up the oxytocin that

01:04:44.680 --> 01:04:47.320 align:middle line:84%
will lower the testosterone
and bring her back to estrogen

01:04:47.320 --> 01:04:49.270 align:middle line:84%
or progesterone, which
is the hormones she

01:04:49.270 --> 01:04:50.590 align:middle line:90%
needs for well-being.

01:04:50.590 --> 01:04:52.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What about
the mind reading?

01:04:52.090 --> 01:04:54.070 align:middle line:84%
Like, he should have
brought me flowers?

01:04:54.070 --> 01:04:55.660 align:middle line:84%
It would have been so
nice if he would have just

01:04:55.660 --> 01:04:57.702 align:middle line:84%
brought me flow-- he should
have opened the door?

01:04:57.702 --> 01:04:59.320 align:middle line:90%
Why didn't he pay for dinner?

01:04:59.320 --> 01:05:03.250 align:middle line:84%
What about those mind-reads
that we would like to see?

01:05:03.250 --> 01:05:06.055 align:middle line:84%
They got edited out a
long time ago, right?

01:05:06.055 --> 01:05:07.555 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Well, mind
reading is awful.

01:05:07.555 --> 01:05:07.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

01:05:07.900 --> 01:05:10.360 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: OK, you have to see
how you're keeping yourself

01:05:10.360 --> 01:05:11.470 align:middle line:90%
from feeling love.

01:05:11.470 --> 01:05:12.758 align:middle line:90%
But then you feel powerless.

01:05:12.758 --> 01:05:14.800 align:middle line:84%
I'll tell you how Bonnie
got me to bring flowers.

01:05:14.800 --> 01:05:15.950 align:middle line:90%
This is a funny story.

01:05:15.950 --> 01:05:18.668 align:middle line:84%
After a year of marriage,
I stopped bringing flowers.

01:05:18.668 --> 01:05:20.460 align:middle line:84%
So one day, I'm going
out the house to work

01:05:20.460 --> 01:05:22.730 align:middle line:84%
and there was a vase
right by the door.

01:05:22.730 --> 01:05:24.360 align:middle line:84%
And I looked at it
and then walked out.

01:05:24.360 --> 01:05:26.610 align:middle line:84%
Then the next day, there
were three vases by the door.

01:05:26.610 --> 01:05:27.750 align:middle line:90%
I thought, what is that?

01:05:27.750 --> 01:05:29.300 align:middle line:84%
The next day, there
were 12 vases.

01:05:29.300 --> 01:05:31.070 align:middle line:84%
She even borrowed
vases from neighbors.

01:05:31.070 --> 01:05:33.630 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, honey, what
are these vases doing here?

01:05:33.630 --> 01:05:36.720 align:middle line:84%
And she goes, John, what
do you put in vases?

01:05:36.720 --> 01:05:38.830 align:middle line:84%
OK, so that was
cute indirectness.

01:05:38.830 --> 01:05:39.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's great.

01:05:39.630 --> 01:05:41.088 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: But what
we have to realize

01:05:41.088 --> 01:05:43.110 align:middle line:84%
is, as we become
more mature, it's

01:05:43.110 --> 01:05:44.970 align:middle line:84%
important to be
specific and direct.

01:05:44.970 --> 01:05:46.767 align:middle line:90%
And so we had a conversation.

01:05:46.767 --> 01:05:49.350 align:middle line:84%
I said to her, well, honey, if
you want flowers, why don't you

01:05:49.350 --> 01:05:50.760 align:middle line:90%
just buy them?

01:05:50.760 --> 01:05:51.600 align:middle line:90%
She set me straight.

01:05:51.600 --> 01:05:54.930 align:middle line:84%
She says, John, it's not
romantic if I buy them.

01:05:54.930 --> 01:05:55.950 align:middle line:90%
It's the thought.

01:05:55.950 --> 01:05:57.510 align:middle line:84%
If you remember to
bring the flowers,

01:05:57.510 --> 01:05:59.010 align:middle line:90%
it makes me feel special.

01:05:59.010 --> 01:06:00.070 align:middle line:90%
It's sweet.

01:06:00.070 --> 01:06:02.790 align:middle line:84%
And if I have to ask for
it, it's not as special.

01:06:02.790 --> 01:06:04.710 align:middle line:90%
That taught me to do this.

01:06:04.710 --> 01:06:07.560 align:middle line:84%
Bonnie would say to me, on
Monday, she'd say, John,

01:06:07.560 --> 01:06:09.790 align:middle line:84%
I'm getting my hair
done this Thursday.

01:06:09.790 --> 01:06:11.355 align:middle line:84%
Now, my first reaction
is, who cares?

01:06:11.355 --> 01:06:12.800 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

01:06:12.800 --> 01:06:14.037 align:middle line:90%
Then I figured it out.

01:06:14.037 --> 01:06:15.120 align:middle line:90%
Why does she tell me that?

01:06:15.120 --> 01:06:18.050 align:middle line:84%
Oh, she's giving me warning
so that when she comes home,

01:06:18.050 --> 01:06:18.850 align:middle line:90%
I notice.

01:06:18.850 --> 01:06:19.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And you say something.

01:06:19.950 --> 01:06:20.950 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: I say something.

01:06:20.950 --> 01:06:23.610 align:middle line:84%
Because if she has to say,
what do you think of my hair,

01:06:23.610 --> 01:06:26.400 align:middle line:84%
it's not as exciting
as opposed to me,

01:06:26.400 --> 01:06:27.600 align:middle line:90%
oh, you got your haircut.

01:06:27.600 --> 01:06:28.450 align:middle line:90%
It looks great.

01:06:28.450 --> 01:06:29.790 align:middle line:90%
It makes a bigger impact.

01:06:29.790 --> 01:06:32.200 align:middle line:84%
At the same time, it
makes a bigger impact,

01:06:32.200 --> 01:06:33.943 align:middle line:84%
but if a man doesn't
do it, it's not

01:06:33.943 --> 01:06:35.110 align:middle line:90%
because he doesn't love you.

01:06:35.110 --> 01:06:36.318 align:middle line:90%
It's he's not educated.

01:06:36.318 --> 01:06:37.860 align:middle line:84%
So you have to take
this step forward

01:06:37.860 --> 01:06:40.770 align:middle line:84%
to educate him with a little
request, which is, honey,

01:06:40.770 --> 01:06:42.600 align:middle line:84%
when I come home from
getting my hair cut,

01:06:42.600 --> 01:06:45.600 align:middle line:84%
I want you to notice and
say how beautiful I look.

01:06:45.600 --> 01:06:46.560 align:middle line:90%
And then forget it.

01:06:46.560 --> 01:06:48.720 align:middle line:84%
And then it goes
into the computer

01:06:48.720 --> 01:06:50.130 align:middle line:90%
so he can start learning.

01:06:50.130 --> 01:06:52.260 align:middle line:84%
Because men, we
don't consciously

01:06:52.260 --> 01:06:53.800 align:middle line:90%
think that's so important.

01:06:53.800 --> 01:06:56.210 align:middle line:10%
But to me-- like
when I give a talk

01:06:56.210 --> 01:06:59.170 align:middle line:10%
and I get a standing ovation
and I don't have to ask for it,

01:06:59.170 --> 01:07:01.297 align:middle line:10%
it's 1,000 times more
than if I worked for it.

01:07:01.297 --> 01:07:03.630 align:middle line:10%
And every performer knows how
to get a standing ovation.

01:07:03.630 --> 01:07:06.270 align:middle line:84%
You can set it up and
do this, but I refuse to

01:07:06.270 --> 01:07:08.730 align:middle line:84%
so that when I do it, it
was really unsolicited.

01:07:08.730 --> 01:07:10.520 align:middle line:90%
It just came.

01:07:10.520 --> 01:07:11.820 align:middle line:90%
I hold that in my mind.

01:07:11.820 --> 01:07:14.100 align:middle line:84%
What Bonnie wants is for
me to do these things

01:07:14.100 --> 01:07:15.600 align:middle line:90%
without her having to ask.

01:07:15.600 --> 01:07:18.090 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, if
you're not getting it, women,

01:07:18.090 --> 01:07:21.780 align:middle line:84%
you have to start asking till
he learns to do those things.

01:07:21.780 --> 01:07:24.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You had a 35-year
incredible relationship

01:07:24.810 --> 01:07:28.217 align:middle line:84%
with Bonnie, and it was a
monogamous relationship.

01:07:28.217 --> 01:07:30.050 align:middle line:84%
You didn't have an open
relationship, right?

01:07:30.050 --> 01:07:30.850 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: No, no.

01:07:30.850 --> 01:07:33.710 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you had magic
in that relationship, right?

01:07:33.710 --> 01:07:37.012 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Yes, and we still have
the magic, but she's not here.

01:07:37.012 --> 01:07:37.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: She's not here.

01:07:37.970 --> 01:07:38.770 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Physically.

01:07:38.770 --> 01:07:42.020 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, she is
in spirit now with us.

01:07:42.020 --> 01:07:42.820 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Yeah.

01:07:42.820 --> 01:07:45.570 align:middle line:10%
And we wanted to
dedicate this show to her

01:07:45.570 --> 01:07:49.990 align:middle line:10%
because she has been such a
huge influence on our lives.

01:07:49.990 --> 01:07:54.070 align:middle line:10%
She's inspired the greatest
relationship book of all time.

01:07:54.070 --> 01:07:57.500 align:middle line:84%
And we put together a
little in memoriam--

01:07:57.500 --> 01:08:00.210 align:middle line:84%
a beautiful piece here
for you to just take

01:08:00.210 --> 01:08:04.290 align:middle line:84%
a look at this show that's
being honored in Bonnie's name.

01:08:04.290 --> 01:08:05.220 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

01:08:05.220 --> 01:08:06.079 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Thank you.

